SKILL|audiocraft-audio-generation|"AudioCraft: MusicGen text-to-music, AudioGen text-to-sound."
STEP|1|Use AudioCraft when:**
STEP|2|Need to generate music from text descriptions
STEP|3|Creating sound effects and environmental audio
STEP|4|Building music generation applications
STEP|5|Need melody-conditioned music generation
STEP|6|Want stereo audio output
STEP|7|Require controllable music generation with style transfer
STEP|8|Key features:**
STEP|9|**MusicGen**: Text-to-music generation with melody conditioning
STEP|10|**AudioGen**: Text-to-sound effects generation
STEP|11|**EnCodec**: High-fidelity neural audio codec
STEP|12|**Multiple model sizes**: Small (300M) to Large (3.3B)
STEP|13|**Stereo support**: Full stereo audio generation
STEP|14|**Style conditioning**: MusicGen-Style for reference-based generation
STEP|15|Use alternatives instead:**
STEP|16|**Stable Audio**: For longer commercial music generation
STEP|17|**Bark**: For text-to-speech with music/sound effects
STEP|18|**Riffusion**: For spectogram-based music generation
STEP|19|**OpenAI Jukebox**: For raw audio generation with lyrics
STEP|20|**[Advanced Usage](references/advanced-usage.md)** - Training, fine-tuning, deployment
STEP|21|**[Troubleshooting](references/troubleshooting.md)** - Common issues and solutions
STEP|22|**GitHub**: https://github.com/facebookresearch/audiocraft
STEP|23|**Paper (MusicGen)**: https://arxiv.org/abs/2306.05284
STEP|24|**Paper (AudioGen)**: https://arxiv.org/abs/2209.15352
STEP|25|**HuggingFace**: https://huggingface.co/facebook/musicgen-small
STEP|26|**Demo**: https://huggingface.co/spaces/facebook/MusicGen
